  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Humanitarian Air Services in the Kivus  ex-Oriental province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Continued access by the Helicopter to the Kivus amp former Oriental province by UNHAS DRC will facilitate continued humanitarian needs in the region.

The humanitarian situation in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) has deteriorated dramatically over the last year. The crisis has deepened, affecting people in areas previously considered stable such as the Kasai regions. According to OCHA, renewed conflict has forced more than 1.5 million to flee their homes in 2017, an average of 6000 people per day. Today, there are over 3.9 million internally displaced people, currently the highest number in Africa.

The eastern provinces are still affected by tension and violence due to the presence of a growing number of armed groups in North Kivu, South Kivu, Maniema, and Ituri provinces. These provinces are also facing serious inter-ethnic violence such as the ongoing conflict between the Pygmy and Luba communities in Tanganyika province. Widespread attacks on civilians, pillage and burning of villages, rapes and other human rights abuses have led to uninterrupted displacements. 

Resources from CHF will be used to provide air services to the humanitarian community in these regions. The funds will be critical in ensuring that WFP is able to maintain enhanced air services particularly in areas of greatest humanitarian need that are not accessible by fixed wing aircraft.</narrative>
  </description>
